  <title translate="true">Tip #55</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Heading3"><text styleclass="Heading3" translate="true">Tip of the Day</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:0px; cell-spacing:0px; border-width:0px; cell-border-width:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:58px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="TipOfTheDayBulb.jpg" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:328px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">A &quot;</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">zombie&quot;</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> is a hidden view in your image that, for some reason, never correctly became associated with a visible window. &#160;Typically this may happen if an error occurs when the view was being opened. &#160;</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Zombies often keep alive large chains of objects preventing them from being garbage collected. Fortunately, one can easily get rid of most zombies using the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Panic</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> button in the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">System Folder</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">.</text><snippet src="Tip_Of_The_Day_Footer"/></para>
  </body>
